  "prompt": "Who is the speaker of Rajya Sabha?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, the **Chairman of the Rajya Sabha** (the upper house of India's Parliament) is the **Vice President of India, Jagdeep Dhankhar**. \n\n### Key Points:\n- **Role of the Chairman**: The Chairman presides over the sessions of the Rajya Sabha, ensuring that discussions are conducted in an orderly manner and that the house's rules are followed.\n  \n- **Vice President's Role**: In addition to being the ceremonial second-highest constitutional office in India, the Vice President serves as the ex-officio Chairman of the Rajya Sabha. This role is analogous to the Speaker in the Lok Sabha (the lower house).\n\n- **Deputy Chairman**: In the absence of the Vice President, the Deputy Chairman of the Rajya Sabha presides over the sessions. As of October 2023, the Deputy Chairman is **D. V. Sadananda Gowda**.\n\nIf you have any more questions about the Indian parliamentary system or its members, feel free to ask!",
